org.knime.core.data.blob

Class BinaryObjectCellFactory

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.knime.core.data.blob.BinaryObjectCellFactory
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    DataCellFactory, DataCellFactory.FromInputStream

    public final class BinaryObjectCellFactory
extends Object
implements DataCellFactory.FromInputStream
    Factory to create DataCell objects implementing the BinaryObjectDataValue interface. There should be only one instance of this class per node execution (as files created in the workflow follow a certain naming schema.)

    The cells created by this factory are either instances of BinaryObjectDataCell or BinaryObjectFileStoreDataCell, depending on their size.

    Since:
    2.7
    Author:
    Bernd Wiswedel, KNIME.com, Zurich, Switzerland

      • PROPERTY_MEMORY_LIMIT

        public static final String PROPERTY_MEMORY_LIMIT
        System property to adjust the memory limit for "small" binary object. Default is 4096 bytes. Valid values are count in bytes or values like "1M"

    • Constructor Detail

      • BinaryObjectCellFactory

        public BinaryObjectCellFactory(ExecutionContext exec)
        Create new cell factory based on a node's execution context. The argument object is used to create an extension of FileStoreCell that is used to keep the data for large binary objects.
        Parameters:
        exec - Non-null execution context used to create file store cells (using ExecutionContext.createFileStore(String).

      • BinaryObjectCellFactory

        public BinaryObjectCellFactory()
        Factory of binary objects, which are not associated with the workflow. This constructor should only be used if a factory is used for temporary, non-persistent objects (e.g. in views).

    • Method Detail

      • init

        public void init(ExecutionContext execContext)
        This method is called once by DataTypeRegistry when a factory instance is created. The default implementation does nothing but implementors can override it a make use of the passed execution context. Note that this method may not be called or called with a null argument. In this case it's allowed to fail when an attempt to create a cell is made and an execution context is required.
        Specified by:
        init in interface DataCellFactory
        Parameters:
        execContext - the current node's execution context, may be null
        Since:
        3.0

        public DataCell create(byte[] bytes)
                throws IOException
        Creates a new cell given a byte array.
        Parameters:
        bytes - The byte array to wrap. Argument must not be null and must not be changed after the call (data is not copied).
        Returns:
